BEGIN CRUMB
v=1.3
kind=task
title=Scoped migration with explicit guardrails
source=claude.agent
project=web-app
---
[goal]
Migrate the user.settings schema from JSON to TOML without touching deploy.

[context]
- Settings are currently stored in user_settings.json.
- Target format: TOML, with a backfill script.

[constraints]
- Preserve existing setting keys
- Do not change the public API shape

[guardrails]
- type=tool      deny=shell-exec          why=security boundary
- type=scope     max=files=5              why=token budget for the handoff
- type=verify    require=tests            why=regression prevention
- type=approval  action=merge  who=human  why=schema change touches prod data

[invariants]
- schema version bumps monotonically
- existing user_settings.json rows still validate during rollout
END CRUMB
